<Link id="l00105" /><CodeLine lineNumber="105"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Implementation of format&#95;provider&lt;T&gt; for integral arithmetic types.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00106" /><CodeLine lineNumber="106"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00107" /><CodeLine lineNumber="107"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The options string of an integral type has the grammar:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00108" /><CodeLine lineNumber="108"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00109" /><CodeLine lineNumber="109"><Highlight kind="comment">///   integer&#95;options   :: &#91;style&#93;&#91;digits&#93;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00110" /><CodeLine lineNumber="110"><Highlight kind="comment">///   style             :: &lt;see table below&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00111" /><CodeLine lineNumber="111"><Highlight kind="comment">///   digits            :: &lt;non-negative integer&gt; 0-99</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00112" /><CodeLine lineNumber="112"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00113" /><CodeLine lineNumber="113"><Highlight kind="comment">///   ==========================================================================</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00114" /><CodeLine lineNumber="114"><Highlight kind="comment">///   |  style  |     Meaning          |      Example     | Digits Meaning     |</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00115" /><CodeLine lineNumber="115"><Highlight kind="comment">///   --------------------------------------------------------------------------</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00116" /><CodeLine lineNumber="116"><Highlight kind="comment">///   |         |                      |  Input |  Output |                    |</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00117" /><CodeLine lineNumber="117"><Highlight kind="comment">///   ==========================================================================</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00118" /><CodeLine lineNumber="118"><Highlight kind="comment">///   |   x-    | Hex no prefix, lower |   42   |    2a   | Minimum # digits   |</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00119" /><CodeLine lineNumber="119"><Highlight kind="comment">///   |   X-    | Hex no prefix, upper |   42   |    2A   | Minimum # digits   |</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00120" /><CodeLine lineNumber="120"><Highlight kind="comment">///   | x+ / x  | Hex + prefix, lower  |   42   |   42  | Minimum # digits   |</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00121" /><CodeLine lineNumber="121"><Highlight kind="comment">///   | X+ / X  | Hex + prefix, upper  |   42   |   42  | Minimum # digits   |</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00122" /><CodeLine lineNumber="122"><Highlight kind="comment">///   | N / n   | Digit grouped number | 123456 | 123,456 | Ignored            |</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00123" /><CodeLine lineNumber="123"><Highlight kind="comment">///   | D / d   | Integer              | 100000 | 100000  | Ignored            |</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00124" /><CodeLine lineNumber="124"><Highlight kind="comment">///   | (empty) | Same as D / d        |        |         |                    |</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00125" /><CodeLine lineNumber="125"><Highlight kind="comment">///   ==========================================================================</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00154" /><CodeLine lineNumber="154"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Implementation of format&#95;provider&lt;T&gt; for integral pointer types.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00155" /><CodeLine lineNumber="155"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00156" /><CodeLine lineNumber="156"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The options string of a pointer type has the grammar:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00157" /><CodeLine lineNumber="157"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00158" /><CodeLine lineNumber="158"><Highlight kind="comment">///   pointer&#95;options   :: &#91;style&#93;&#91;precision&#93;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00159" /><CodeLine lineNumber="159"><Highlight kind="comment">///   style             :: &lt;see table below&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00160" /><CodeLine lineNumber="160"><Highlight kind="comment">///   digits            :: &lt;non-negative integer&gt; 0-sizeof(void&#42;)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00161" /><CodeLine lineNumber="161"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00162" /><CodeLine lineNumber="162"><Highlight kind="comment">///   ==========================================================================</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00163" /><CodeLine lineNumber="163"><Highlight kind="comment">///   |   S     |     Meaning          |                Example                |</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00164" /><CodeLine lineNumber="164"><Highlight kind="comment">///   --------------------------------------------------------------------------</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00165" /><CodeLine lineNumber="165"><Highlight kind="comment">///   |         |                      |       Input       |      Output       |</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00166" /><CodeLine lineNumber="166"><Highlight kind="comment">///   ==========================================================================</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00167" /><CodeLine lineNumber="167"><Highlight kind="comment">///   |   x-    | Hex no prefix, lower |    3735928559     |     deadbeef      |</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00168" /><CodeLine lineNumber="168"><Highlight kind="comment">///   |   X-    | Hex no prefix, upper |    3735928559     |     DEADBEEF      |</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00169" /><CodeLine lineNumber="169"><Highlight kind="comment">///   | x+ / x  | Hex + prefix, lower  |    3735928559     |    3735928559     |</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00170" /><CodeLine lineNumber="170"><Highlight kind="comment">///   | X+ / X  | Hex + prefix, upper  |    3735928559     |    3735928559     |</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00171" /><CodeLine lineNumber="171"><Highlight kind="comment">///   | (empty) | Same as X+ / X       |                   |                   |</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00172" /><CodeLine lineNumber="172"><Highlight kind="comment">///   ==========================================================================</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00173" /><CodeLine lineNumber="173"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00174" /><CodeLine lineNumber="174"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The default precision is the number of nibbles in a machine word, and in all</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00175" /><CodeLine lineNumber="175"><Highlight kind="comment">/// cases indicates the minimum number of nibbles to print.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00191" /><CodeLine lineNumber="191"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Implementation of format&#95;provider&lt;T&gt; for c-style strings and string</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00192" /><CodeLine lineNumber="192"><Highlight kind="comment">/// objects such as std::string and llvm::StringRef.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00193" /><CodeLine lineNumber="193"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00194" /><CodeLine lineNumber="194"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The options string of a string type has the grammar:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00195" /><CodeLine lineNumber="195"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00196" /><CodeLine lineNumber="196"><Highlight kind="comment">///   string&#95;options :: &#91;length&#93;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00197" /><CodeLine lineNumber="197"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00198" /><CodeLine lineNumber="198"><Highlight kind="comment">/// where &#96;length&#96; is an optional integer specifying the maximum number of</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00199" /><CodeLine lineNumber="199"><Highlight kind="comment">/// characters in the string to print.  If &#96;length&#96; is omitted, the string is</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00200" /><CodeLine lineNumber="200"><Highlight kind="comment">/// printed up to the null terminator.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00278" /><CodeLine lineNumber="278"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Implementation of format&#95;provider&lt;T&gt; for floating point types.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00279" /><CodeLine lineNumber="279"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00280" /><CodeLine lineNumber="280"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The options string of a floating point type has the format:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00281" /><CodeLine lineNumber="281"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00282" /><CodeLine lineNumber="282"><Highlight kind="comment">///   float&#95;options   :: &#91;style&#93;&#91;precision&#93;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00283" /><CodeLine lineNumber="283"><Highlight kind="comment">///   style           :: &lt;see table below&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00284" /><CodeLine lineNumber="284"><Highlight kind="comment">///   precision       :: &lt;non-negative integer&gt; 0-99</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00285" /><CodeLine lineNumber="285"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00286" /><CodeLine lineNumber="286"><Highlight kind="comment">///   =====================================================</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00287" /><CodeLine lineNumber="287"><Highlight kind="comment">///   |  style  |     Meaning          |      Example     |</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00288" /><CodeLine lineNumber="288"><Highlight kind="comment">///   -----------------------------------------------------</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00289" /><CodeLine lineNumber="289"><Highlight kind="comment">///   |         |                      |  Input |  Output |</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00290" /><CodeLine lineNumber="290"><Highlight kind="comment">///   =====================================================</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00291" /><CodeLine lineNumber="291"><Highlight kind="comment">///   | P / p   | Percentage           |  0.05  |  5.00%  |</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00292" /><CodeLine lineNumber="292"><Highlight kind="comment">///   | F / f   | Fixed point          |   1  |  1   |</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00293" /><CodeLine lineNumber="293"><Highlight kind="comment">///   |   E     | Exponential with E   | 100000 | 100000 |</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00294" /><CodeLine lineNumber="294"><Highlight kind="comment">///   |   e     | Exponential with e   | 100000 | 100000 |</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00295" /><CodeLine lineNumber="295"><Highlight kind="comment">///   | (empty) | Same as F / f        |        |         |</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00296" /><CodeLine lineNumber="296"><Highlight kind="comment">///   =====================================================</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00297" /><CodeLine lineNumber="297"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00298" /><CodeLine lineNumber="298"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The default precision is 6 for exponential (E / e) and 2 for everything</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00299" /><CodeLine lineNumber="299"><Highlight kind="comment">/// else.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00300" /><CodeLine lineNumber="300"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00301" /><CodeLine lineNumber="301"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">template</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &lt;</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">typename</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> T&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00302" /><CodeLine lineNumber="302" lineLink="/docs/api/structs/llvm/format-provider-0f8c4dae2a93fb42cc485d5a034bb90a"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">struct </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/format-provider">format&#95;provider</a>&lt;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00339" /><CodeLine lineNumber="339"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Implementation of format&#95;provider&lt;T&gt; for ranges.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00340" /><CodeLine lineNumber="340"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00341" /><CodeLine lineNumber="341"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This will print an arbitrary range as a delimited sequence of items.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00342" /><CodeLine lineNumber="342"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00343" /><CodeLine lineNumber="343"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The options string of a range type has the grammar:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00344" /><CodeLine lineNumber="344"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00345" /><CodeLine lineNumber="345"><Highlight kind="comment">///   range&#95;style       ::= &#91;separator&#93; &#91;element&#95;style&#93;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00346" /><CodeLine lineNumber="346"><Highlight kind="comment">///   separator         ::= &quot;$&quot; delimeted&#95;expr</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00347" /><CodeLine lineNumber="347"><Highlight kind="comment">///   element&#95;style     ::= &quot;@&quot; delimeted&#95;expr</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00348" /><CodeLine lineNumber="348"><Highlight kind="comment">///   delimeted&#95;expr    ::= &quot;&#91;&quot; expr &quot;&#93;&quot; | &quot;(&quot; expr &quot;)&quot; | &quot;&lt;&quot; expr &quot;&gt;&quot;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00349" /><CodeLine lineNumber="349"><Highlight kind="comment">///   expr              ::= &lt;any string not containing delimeter&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00350" /><CodeLine lineNumber="350"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00351" /><CodeLine lineNumber="351"><Highlight kind="comment">/// where the separator expression is the string to insert between consecutive</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00352" /><CodeLine lineNumber="352"><Highlight kind="comment">/// items in the range and the argument expression is the Style specification to</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00353" /><CodeLine lineNumber="353"><Highlight kind="comment">/// be used when formatting the underlying type.  The default separator if</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00354" /><CodeLine lineNumber="354"><Highlight kind="comment">/// unspecified is &#39; &#39; (space).  The syntax of the argument expression follows</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00355" /><CodeLine lineNumber="355"><Highlight kind="comment">/// whatever grammar is dictated by the format provider or format adapter used</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00356" /><CodeLine lineNumber="356"><Highlight kind="comment">/// to format the value type.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00357" /><CodeLine lineNumber="357"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00358" /><CodeLine lineNumber="358"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Note that attempting to format an &#96;iterator&#95;range&lt;T&gt;&#96; where no format</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00359" /><CodeLine lineNumber="359"><Highlight kind="comment">/// provider can be found for T will result in a compile error.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00360" /><CodeLine lineNumber="360"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00361" /><CodeLine lineNumber="361"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00362" /><CodeLine lineNumber="362" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/format-provider-5361e6bb4a56f61bc90e5b264ca769ca"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">template</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &lt;</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">typename</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> IterT&gt; </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">class </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/format-provider">format&#95;provider</a>&lt;<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm">llvm</a>::<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/iterator-range">iterator&#95;range</a>&lt;IterT&gt;&gt; &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
